Hillcrest Laboratories, Inc.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 22, 2017 3:49 AM ET
Software

Company Overview of Hillcrest Laboratories, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Hillcrest Laboratories, Inc., also known as Hillcrest Labs, Inc., engages in the supply of software and hardware based on a Freespace technology that transforms sensor data into contextual & application-ready motion information. It offers MotionEngine smart TV, a sensor fusion software that brings cursor, gesture & motion control to smart TVs and their peripherals; MotionEngine mobile, a motion software package that delivers sensor independent motion processing for smartphones, tablets, and other mobile devices; MotionEngine Lite, a motion software package that provides in-air cursor control with a minimized footprint; and MotionEngine Universal, a motion software package that enhances and d...
Hillcrest Laboratories, Inc., also known as Hillcrest Labs, Inc., engages in the supply of software and hardware based on a Freespace technology that transforms sensor data into contextual & application-ready motion information. It offers MotionEngine smart TV, a sensor fusion software that brings cursor, gesture & motion control to smart TVs and their peripherals; MotionEngine mobile, a motion software package that delivers sensor independent motion processing for smartphones, tablets, and other mobile devices; MotionEngine Lite, a motion software package that provides in-air cursor control with a minimized footprint; and MotionEngine Universal, a motion software package that enhances and differentiates various products through motion, gesture, and cursor control.It also provides SH-1, an intelligent sensor hub software stack that makes context aware sensing possible in mobile, wearable, & Internet of Things devices; Freespace sensor modules, which are inertial measurement units/attitude heading reference systems; Scoop pointer remote; Scoop wireless presenter. In addition, it offers consulting services in the areas of product testing and optimization, sensor selection consultation, and user interface improvement, as well as in the areas of motion integration that include hardware design, motion system optimization, user interface consultation, and application design and development. Further, the company offers software tools to accelerate development and prototyping with the Freespace MotionEngine. Hillcrest Laboratories, Inc. was formerly known as Hillcrest Communications, Inc. and changed its name to Hillcrest Laboratories, Inc. in August 2005. The company was founded in 2001 and is based in Rockville, Maryland. As of December 20, 2016, Hillcrest Laboratories, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of InterDigital, Inc.
